      • parseFile

        public void parseFile()
               throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                      java.io.IOException
        Takes input from the file located at fileName, runs through the data and sorts it into a HashMap dataCatalog that holds data for each data type. It then calculates statistics for all data types.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - In case of an incorrect directory.
        java.io.IOException - In case of an improperly formatted file.
